main event: A civilian observed an object shaped like a frankfurter, tumbling end over end in the sky, in Arlington, Massachusetts on December 1, 1962.
interesting points: The object was red in color and appeared to be flying at a 30-degree elevation in the southwest., The sighting lasted approximately 3-5 minutes., The observer attempted to call for help but was unable to get through., The object was described as tumbling end over end during its flight., It was concluded that the sighting probably involved a high-flying jet due to unobserved sun caused by clouds.
